creator: George MacDonald
description:
LibriVox recording of Annals of a Quiet Neighbourhood by George MacDonald.

Read in English by Lee Smalley; Greg Giordano; geoffbl; Lynne Thompson; Bill Boerst; Larry Wilson; noblesavage; Eric Metzler; Gertrude Durette; and ToddHW.

This delightful story begins in a little town called Marshmallows, where a young man, the new vicar, Harry Walton, has just arrived. As he begins his work Harry realizes that everything is not quite 'right' in his little parish and it all seems to center around Oldcastle Hall. As he wins the affection of the people secrets begin to unfold, and Harry Walton attempts to free them from guilt of the past, help them overcome pride and while he is at it, he falls in love with a woman who's past is the most mysterious yet, and Who's tyrannical mother is the mistress of Oldcastle Hall.

This Is a wonderful, heartwarming, romance and a unique mystery, told from the viewpoint of the young vicar. (Summary by Fiddlesticks )

For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

M4B Format Available
